61
00:03:48.700 --> 00:03:50.120
for pediatric cancer research.

62
00:03:51.040 --> 00:03:54.960
She's invented the gene expression-based high-throughput screening, a chemical

63
00:03:55.040 --> 00:03:58.800
genomic strategy that informed the Broad Institute's Connectivity Map and

64
00:03:58.900 --> 00:04:02.160
influenced expression-based discovery approaches more broadly.

65
00:04:02.800 --> 00:04:06.670
She also co-led the first generation of the Pediatric Dependency

66
00:04:06.760 --> 00:04:10.500
Map, which has become a major public resource for identifying therapeutic

67
00:04:10.540 --> 00:04:14.380
vulnerabilities across childhood cancers. Importantly, Dr.

68
00:04:14.500 --> 00:04:18.280
Stegmaier's work has translated her genomic discoveries into clinical

69
00:04:18.421 --> 00:04:22.000
impact. Together with colleagues, she established the Leukemia

70
00:04:22.079 --> 00:04:25.740
Precision Therapy Consortium, also known as LEAP, the first US

71
00:04:25.780 --> 00:04:29.760
multi-institutional genomics-based clinical study for children with relapsed or

72
00:04:29.800 --> 00:04:33.740
refractory leukemia. And her work has also contributed to multiple

73
00:04:33.780 --> 00:04:36.930
clinical trials for children with a wide variety of cancers.

74
00:04:37.720 --> 00:04:39.610
Beyond her scientific accomplishments, Dr.

75
00:04:39.880 --> 00:04:42.890
Stegmaier is a highly respected leader and mentor.

76
00:04:43.440 --> 00:04:47.260
She has served as chair of the St. Jude Scientific Advisory Board, chair

77
00:04:47.480 --> 00:04:51.380
of the AACR Pediatric Cancer Working Group, and as a member of the

78
00:04:51.440 --> 00:04:55.310
AACR Board of Directors, where she represents pediatrics extremely well.

79
00:04:56.340 --> 00:05:00.180
She's deeply committed to training the next generation of researchers, many of

80
00:05:00.220 --> 00:05:03.770
whom now lead independent laboratories and hold leadership roles in

81
00:05:03.770 --> 00:05:07.500
academia and industry. Her many honors include election to the

82
00:05:07.520 --> 00:05:11.400
Association of American Physicians

83
