00:07:42.324 --> 00:07:46.004
illustrating how the technologies have really impacted this

123
00:07:46.064 --> 00:07:49.584
field and how they'll continue to impact the field going forward.

124
00:07:49.624 --> 00:07:53.364
And so my first involvement in laboratory-based

125
00:07:53.444 --> 00:07:57.284
investigation was during my medical school days at Harvard,

126
00:07:57.964 --> 00:08:01.264
where I participated in the Howard Hughes Medical Student Program.

127
00:08:01.704 --> 00:08:03.684
And I worked in Gary Gilliland's lab.

