00:46:40.184 --> 00:46:44.164
activator that it may be harder to actually repress that fusion output than it

770
00:46:44.264 --> 00:46:47.844
is to activate expression at a target that's repressed.

771
00:46:47.884 --> 00:46:51.384
And so we don't have, I would say this is our NO1 study.

772
00:46:51.444 --> 00:46:54.864
We don't have lots more data to address that, but that was our observation.

773
00:46:55.024 --> 00:46:58.204
BCL6 is there, but it's not really repressing.

774
00:46:58.924 --> 00:47:01.114
You might also have a stoichiometry problem, right?

775
00:47:01.144 --> 00:47:01.463
That's possible.

776
00:47:01.484 --> 00:47:02.864
Because of multi-binding.

777
00:47:02.963 --> 00:47:04.984
Absolutely. Yep. A great question.

